@page "/help/administration"
@attribute [Authorize]

<PageTitle>Administration</PageTitle>

<section class="page-shell">
    <header class="page-header">
        <div>
            <p class="eyebrow">Administration</p>
            <h1>Protect the data, keep releases clean, and make support repeatable.</h1>
        </div>
        <p class="page-intro">
            Administrative work includes account hygiene, key management, publish discipline, data handling, and making
            sure operators can trust the environment they work in every day.
        </p>
    </header>

    <section class="content-grid">
        <article class="panel">
            <h2>Security baseline</h2>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li>Require authenticated access before loading accounting data.</li>
                <li>Keep password hashes and protected fields under managed operational control.</li>
                <li>Remove stale operator access promptly and review who needs what.</li>
                <li>Plan for stronger role enforcement, audit logging, and externalized secrets before production use.</li>
            </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="panel">
            <h2>Data and source control</h2>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li>Local application data and fallback SQLite storage stay out of Git.</li>
                <li>Source-controlled static assets belong under <code>BrassLedger.Web/wwwroot</code>.</li>
                <li>Publish output under <code>artifacts</code> is disposable and should be regenerated when needed.</li>
                <li>Package builds as releases rather than committing generated files to the main repository.</li>
            </ul>
        </article>
    </section>

    <section class="panel">
        <h2>Recommended admin checklist</h2>
        <ol class="step-list">
            <li>Review open issues, failed tests, and operator blockers.</li>
            <li>Confirm authentication, configuration, and environment assumptions are still valid.</li>
            <li>Build and test from source before publishing.</li>
            <li>Publish for the intended platform and smoke-test the result.</li>
            <li>Update help content whenever operator-visible behavior changes.</li>
        </ol>
    </section>
</section>
